&lt;p>Grubby vs Flash MLG Result&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Prince Charmings: Riot Comic Contest Entry</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/illustration/prince-charmings-riot-comic-contest-entry/</link><pubDate>Fri, 07 Sep 2012 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/illustration/prince-charmings-riot-comic-contest-entry/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/comic_with_text.jpg">&lt;img src="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/comic_with_text.jpg" alt="comic_with_text" title="comic_with_text">&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>I entered a League of Legends comic contest held by riot games.  It was very entertaining and a fun way to flex some creative muscle.  Interestingly the most difficult part of the comic is creating something that would be funny and fit within the guidelines.  The challenge proved to be very fun and rewarding.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>  Writing the comic is definitely a skill in itself.  At first I had Photoshop loaded up and I was using text boxes to attempt to create my story.  I soon realized I was a bit bolder than I should have, and reverted to ye ‘ole notepad to iron out the concept.  Once again proving that preplanning smart design is an artists best friend.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>